node.text: Omg y’all.....add this to the list of crazy things we used to do before Rona! This was exactly 1 year ago and little did I know I was documenting the very last time I went out grocery shopping with both kids 😂😂 Let’s just say I didn’t need a pandemic to tell me not to do that again!

node.text:
So I got up this morning to get the kids ready and realized I forgot to buy milk last night 😱 Then I remembered the instant porridges that the lovely team at @gracefoods gave to me and I thought well they can eat this! It was their first time trying it and they loved it! You know I always make porridge for them so if they liked this, then it must be really good! Definitely adding this to my list of quick breakfasts for those school mornings when I’m short on time! .
.

node.text:
Who’s coming? Pull up on this jerk shrimp with rasta pasta and enjoy yourself. I devein both the top and underside of the shrimp. Deveining the underside isn’t necessary but it resembles the the top side and I just can’t 😩 Cook the shrimp first, remove it from the pot and cook the pasta in the same pot. It’ll catch the leftover seasoning and put somebody right to bed 😉 
.
.
.

Air fry your corn with seasoning & melted butter! 🔥🔥The barby fried chicken is in my ebook “Irie Delights” which is now on sale with the biggest markdown ever! Enjoy 30%off!!! No code needed!! node.text:
If you see me making oxtail rasta pasta just know I’m either sorry for something (😂) or I’m showing Greg my appreciation for being such a bomb husband ♥️ If you don’t have any browning….no browning, no problem! I caramelized a lil brown sugar before i put the oxtail in and slow cooked it 2 hrs. A true labor of love but oxtail is always worth it. 
.
.

node.text:
I don’t know about you guys but towards the end of the week I am almost running on E! I don’t want to spend hours cooking an elaborate meal. I want to get in and get out so I whipped up this Sweet n Sour chicken! I tweaked it by adding onions & peppers and used Pineapple Ginger juice for the sauce. The market didn’t have diced breasts so I did it myself. I told the kids this was chicken nuggets with Sweet n Sour sauce 😂😂😂 They even snuck a few before I added it to the sauce. Dinner in 30 minutes 😎 You can swap the chicken breast for pork, you can swap in pineapple mango juice or orange juice, and you can use the sweet n sour sauce as a dipping sauce as well. 
.
.
.
Recipe is now on SALE‼️ Inside my ebook “Dinner in 30” available for immediate download at shopthatnursecancook.com (link in bio) Take 25% off! No code needed!

node.text:
One day, early in my career I remember attending the delivery of a micro preemie. She weighed about 500g, just a little over 1 lb. I was her primary nurse for 4 months. I was there when she took her first breath, when she could finally breathe on her own for the first time, saw her through every set back and every triumph. I was even a listening ear when her mom grew frustrated with their NICU journey. The first time her mom was able to hold her and place her skin to skin was an emotional moment for us all. The first time she ate from a bottle was a huge production and I remember her not even wanting anything to do with milk, bottles, or even pacifiers. But she went home in her mom’s arms. Chugging down 2 ounces like a champ and breathing on her own. Today she’s a happy and healthy 6 year old and her peers can hardly keep up with her. Preemies are so inspirational and I’m so blessed to have been a part of their NICU journey as well as the journey of countless preemies and neonates. Happy Neonatal Nurse’s Week 💜
.
.
.
.
